                     <note type="general">Location: Ann Arbor</note>
                     <note type="lines">13 lines + 2 lines written vertically in the right margin</note>
                     <note type="paleography">The text is written in a cursive hand; the letters are sloping to the right. The scribe wrote the (last?) two lines in the right margin writing from down upwards. Before the greeting "chairein" there is blank space of c. 1,5 cm.</note>
                     <note type="recto_verso">Source of description: recto</note>
